name: cyclobutane, methylene-
Reason: 1,3-butadiene has a melting point of -108.9°C. The basic unit for comparison is cyclobutane, which has a melting point of -120.0°C. The methylene- bridge introduces a double bond, which increases the melting point due to increased rigidity and pi-pi interactions. Each double bond can be estimated to add approximately +10°C to the melting point.
